'''Sarachnis''', the mother of the [[temple spider]]s, is a mid-level boss found in the [[Forthos Dungeon]], in a former burial tomb south of the Spider Den. She can be killed as part of a [[spider]] [[Slayer task]].

She is primarily killed for the [[Sarachnis cudgel]], a non-degradeable crush weapon and the [[pristine spider silk]], used to upgrade the [[herb sack]] into the [[Silklined herb sack]], which stores even more herbs. Other drops include the [[giant egg sac]], which is one of the few consistent sources of non-Wilderness [[red spiders' egg]]s and improved drop rates of Forthos Dungeon-unique items. Most notably, Sarachnis has a very high drop rate of [[clue scroll (elite)|elite clue scroll]]s for the relative time it takes to defeat her compared to other content.

The player has the option of fighting her in the normal room or in an instance via the [[Thick Web|thick web]] opening to her lair. An instance costs 25,000 coins, or 12,500 after claiming the rewards from the hard tier of [[Combat Achievements]]. Payment for an instance will be taken from the player's bank.

