==Trivia==
*Upon examining the [[egg sac]]s in Sarachnis' lair, the chatbox will state {{mes|It's making sounds inside. It's going to hatch soon!}} This is the verbatim message that is given upon checking the status of a Pokémon egg that will hatch soon in ''Pokémon Gold'', ''Silver'', and ''Crystal''.
*Sarachnis was originally going to be an instanced solo boss, but was reworked into a non-instanced boss in a [[multicombat area]] after player complaints about the abundance of bosses being fought in instances already.
**An instanced option for Sarachnis was added on [[Update:Cow Boss is Out Today!|25 February 2026]] after passing a [[Poll:Getting Around Poll|poll]], roughly six and a half years after release.
*Her food drop, [[egg potato]]es, could be thematically interpreted as a food made from spider eggs.
*Sarachnis is one of the few [[NPCs]] in the game that can sprint. Whenever she uses her web attack, she sprints to her next location moving 2 tiles per tick. This makes hitting her while she moves very inconsistent as her model is not representative of where she is.
* Contrary to popular belief, Sarachnis' body is not a recoloured [[Chompy bird#Dead|dead chompy bird]], despite their visual similarities.{{CiteReddit|author=Mod West|url=https://www.reddit.com/r/2007scape/comments/owb1fv/comment/h7lqoie/|title=Fun fact: Mod Husky used chompy bird’s model as the body while desingning sarachnis.|quote=This comes up often but it’s honestly just a coincidence. I sat next to Mod Gee when she made it and I don’t recall chompy birds ever coming up and highly doubt it’s something she would’ve done intentionally.|date=3 August 2021|archiveurl=https://archive.ph/OxK5n|archivedate=15 April 2025}}

